{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-note-js","path":"/macos-touchid-sudo/","result":{"data":{"remark":{"fields":{"path":"macos-touchid-sudo"},"meta":{"title":""},"headings":[{"value":"MacOS use TouchID for sudo"}],"html":"<h1>MacOS use TouchID for sudo</h1>\n<p>Thanks to <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qOrlYzqXPa8\">50 macOS Tips and Tricks Using Terminal (the last one is CRAZY!)</a> here is an trick</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">vim</span> /etc/pam.d/sudo</code></pre></div>\n<p>and add at the top:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">auth sufficient pam_tid.so</code></pre></div>\n<p>and after that whenever sudo will ask you for a password you may use your finger</p>"}},"pageContext":{"id":"6b7dea71-3d1c-529f-9332-34e52af33430"}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}